This product includes work authored by Sylvain Cormier
<sylvain@paraxiom.org>, founder of Paraxiom Technologies Inc.

The architecture described herein draws on:

  - The QuantumHarmony post-quantum L1 chain (Paraxiom Technologies),
    which itself extends the polkadot-sdk (Parity Technologies,
    Apache 2.0) with PQ signature size accommodations and the
    parity-scale-codec fork.

  - The Paraxiom-V.I.A. augmented-democracy framework, a joint effort
    of Paraxiom Technologies Inc. and V.I.A. Solutions (Olivier
    Garand), aimed at transparent multi-stakeholder governance for
    cities and enterprises.

  - NIST post-quantum cryptography standards FIPS 203 (ML-KEM),
    FIPS 204 (ML-DSA), and FIPS 205 (SLH-DSA), published 13 August
    2024.

  - W3C Verifiable Credentials Data Model 2.0 (Recommendation,
    15 May 2025) and OpenID for Verifiable Credentials 1.0 (Final,
    July 2025).

